docs.abstract: Developments on the president’s travel ban and efforts to end the Deferred Action for Childhood Arrivals program signal that he could find a new way to counter the legal resistance to his crackdown.
docs.snippet: Developments on the president’s travel ban and efforts to end the Deferred Action for Childhood Arrivals program signal that he could find a new way to counter the legal resistance to his crackdown.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Two back-to-back court developments this week indicate a possible road map for President Trump through the minefield of legal resistance he has faced as judges across the country have blocked much of his hard-line immigration agenda.

headline.main: Courts Give Trump a Possible Path Through a Legal Minefield on Immigration

docs.abstract: Boxed out of budget negotiations, Mick Mulvaney’s second job running the Consumer Financial Protection Bureau represents a second chance for him to leave his mark.
docs.snippet: Boxed out of budget negotiations, Mick Mulvaney’s second job running the Consumer Financial Protection Bureau represents a second chance for him to leave his mark.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — In his time in the Trump administration, Mick Mulvaney has produced two budgets that slashed federal spending and were heralded as blueprints for the deconstruction of the administrative state. Even Republicans ignored them, and Congress then added billions to the very programs he targeted in what seemed a personal rebuke.

headline.main: ‘Like a Mosquito in a Nudist Colony’: How Mick Mulvaney Found Plenty to Target at Consumer Bureau
headline.print_headline: Budget Hawk Hones Claws At Top of Consumer Bureau

docs.abstract: On Thursday, President Trump swapped his role as grim-faced statesman for one that comes more naturally to him: campaign trail firebrand.
docs.snippet: On Thursday, President Trump swapped his role as grim-faced statesman for one that comes more naturally to him: campaign trail firebrand.
docs.lead_paragraph: ELKHART, Ind. — After days of high-stakes negotiations with foreign governments, President Trump traveled to a rally here Thursday night, briefly swapping his role as grim-faced statesman for one that comes more naturally to him: campaign trail firebrand.

headline.main: ‘America Is Respected Again,’ Trump Says in Elkhart, Ind., a City Obama Once Championed
headline.print_headline: ‘America Is Respected Again,’ Trump Declares at Rally

docs.abstract: The study, from two professors at Harvard Law School, also found that women fared better before Republican appointees than Democratic ones.
docs.snippet: The study, from two professors at Harvard Law School, also found that women fared better before Republican appointees than Democratic ones.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Judges appointed by Republican presidents gave longer sentences to black defendants and shorter ones to women than judges appointed by Democrats, according to a new study that analyzed data on more than half a million defendants.

headline.main: Black Defendants Get Longer Sentences From Republican-Appointed Judges, Study Finds
headline.print_headline: Republican-Appointed Judges Give Longer Terms to Blacks, Study Finds

docs.abstract: The U.S. had a trade surplus with Canada of $12.5 billion in 2016. But during a fund-raiser in Missouri on Wednesday, the president recounted ignoring that reality in a meeting with Justin Trudeau.
docs.snippet: The U.S. had a trade surplus with Canada of $12.5 billion in 2016. But during a fund-raiser in Missouri on Wednesday, the president recounted ignoring that reality in a meeting with Justin Trudeau.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump repeated on Thursday his false assertion that the United States runs a trade deficit with Canada, the morning after privately telling Republican donors that he had deliberately insisted on that claim in a meeting with Prime Minister Justin Trudeau of Canada without knowing whether it was true.

headline.main: Trump Repeats False Claim About Canada After Admitting Uncertainty Over Figure
headline.print_headline: Trump Repeats False Claim About Trade With Canada

docs.abstract: Two embattled cabinet secretaries — Ben Carson and David Shulkin — remained in their jobs Friday. The absence of any formal announcements suggested an effort to tamp down the anxiety in the West Wing.
docs.snippet: Two embattled cabinet secretaries — Ben Carson and David Shulkin — remained in their jobs Friday. The absence of any formal announcements suggested an effort to tamp down the anxiety in the West Wing.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump made no immediate moves on Friday to dismiss members of his administration, despite continuing reports of an impending shake-up that have unsettled the White House.

headline.main: Despite Speculation, Trump’s Cabinet Remains Intact

docs.abstract: In a pair of letters to four Middle East nations, President Trump repeated his complaints that the United States has borne too much of the burden in the region.
docs.snippet: In a pair of letters to four Middle East nations, President Trump repeated his complaints that the United States has borne too much of the burden in the region.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump sent two private letters to Middle East allies in recent weeks complaining that the United States has spent too much money in the region and urging them to pick up more of the burden as part of a coalition to counter Iran’s influence, a person familiar with them said Thursday.

headline.main: Trump Presses Arab Allies to Do More to Counter Iran
headline.print_headline: Trump Presses Arab Allies To Do More to Contain Iran

docs.abstract: Ms. DeVos, the education secretary, said in a hearing that guns were “not part of the commission’s charge,” prompting senators to ask how the panel could avoid the subject.
docs.snippet: Ms. DeVos, the education secretary, said in a hearing that guns were “not part of the commission’s charge,” prompting senators to ask how the panel could avoid the subject.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Education Secretary Betsy DeVos told a Senate committee on Tuesday that the federal commission on school safety set up this year after the Parkland, Fla., school massacre will not focus on the role guns play in school violence.

headline.main: Trump’s School Safety Commission Won’t Look at Guns, Betsy DeVos Says
headline.print_headline: DeVos Says New Panel To Assess School Safety  Won’t Focus on Guns

docs.abstract: An Obama-era plan to put Tubman on the $20 has languished under the Trump administration, which said that “neither the final designs nor all features have been finalized.”
docs.snippet: An Obama-era plan to put Tubman on the $20 has languished under the Trump administration, which said that “neither the final designs nor all features have been finalized.”
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump has tried to undo as many Obama-era policies as possible during his first 500 days in office, but his administration has remained curiously circumspect when it comes to one of his predecessor’s initiatives: putting Harriet Tubman on the $20 bill.

headline.main: Harriet Tubman on the $20? Trump’s Treasury Dept. Won’t Commit
headline.print_headline: Is Tubman On $20 Bill? Treasury Won’t Say
